comment: Remi is a great Teacher, one of the best the school has to offer and the best Statsitsics professor I have encountered. He makes a challenging class very simple. He gives you all the worksheets you will need for the class just print them out and attend class. It wont be an Easy Abecause you have to study but his exams are replicas of his worksheets

One of the best professors I've ever had. Very knowledgeable in the field. He would make time to meet with me even when I couldn't make it to his regular office hours. I would definitely recommend him to anyone.
Very helpful instructor. He teaches in ways that are comprehensible for students. If you are paying attention in class, you will definitely learn the material.
he clutched it out for me in the end

Sergey doesn't teach well and the language barrier can be a challenge in the classroom because he speaks very softly and asking questions can get very confusing. He also won't give out review material like the other professors. There were several sheets of review-work that we could have had but he would not hand them out even though other profs did
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: He knows the material,and if you ask him a question about anything related to the course, he can answer it. However, his actual teaching ability is lacking and the way that he explains things is hard to comprehend. Because of this, a private tutor or some other way of learning the material is required unless you just naturally understand math.

I don't like his teaching method-if you can even call it that. He reads pre-made notes that he doesn't seem to understand himself and so I just read the textbook and go to PAL sessions. I don't recommend him if you struggle with math but if you like to do work by yourself, then definitely go with him. You can use his class as a time to just watch.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: The course itself is hard, yes. However, if you read the textbook and use study sessions, you should do fairly well. I didn't pay attention in class because he taught very slow and I didn't feel it was productive.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: Sergey is a baller. This man will teach you what you need to know if you are willing to put in effort. He gets a bad wrap like most lower calc teachers because the material is just hard, and you have to deal with common exam times. Just remember to let him know if you dont understand something and he will backtrack to explain it.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: He tries really hard but he just can't seem to teach math effectively. He is very slow, skips examples and will skip material to stay on track. Some how he always manages to get a very high class average (between 2nd and 3rd for all the course sections the semester I took it).
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: very quiet and monotone voice, could be hard to understand if you have trouble understanding people with accents. Not a terrible teacher just needs to be more willing to hear others thoughts.
hes an alright teacher, but the class is especially hard... you will need to go to tutoring to get an A.
A lot of lecturing.
Good teacher overall.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: all he does is lecture, he needs to add something else to this class to make it bearable like group activities or more group quizzes because after a semester of Sergey, you hear the whole world in his voice, which is a beautiful voice, but very monotone...
ratingTags: Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: If you don't read the textbook, you won't pass the class. Sergey is a good lecturer, but you need to really put the effort in to pay attention.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Your pal Leader will be your actual teacher in this class...
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--TEST HEAVY

comment: Sergey gets a bad rap but he really isnt that bad. If you really cant understand the man make sure to go to pal sessions. He does make the class super boring and he is a poor facilitator at best, but he knows what he is doing... I hope...
ratingTags: Respected--Skip class? You won't pass.--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: if you dont want to hate calc, dont take this class. Dont be fooled by the exam averages, my class , including myself, were a bunch of tryhards and we wnet to every pal session, so you better do that too.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY

comment: Boring Lectures, seems like he wants to get out of there everyday, almost like the university is forcing him to teach. not a great experience
If you take this class, you better pray that Hannah Berg is your PAL leader...

He is by far the worst professor I have ever had. Do not take him at all costs. He might have had a high average on the first two exams but I accredit that more to the students knowing how to use khanacademy, youtube, and the textbook. He is hard to understand and does not try to articulate when lecturing.

Sergey spends a lot of time on basic concepts and not enough time on the more complicated ones. He has a thick Russian accent but sometimes he says funny things, like for important topics he says "you should remember this in the middle of the night". He is difficult to listen to because he is very monotone and never seems very happy to be there.

He is the worst teacher I have ever had. He doesn't explain the material well and you are left with a lot of questions. He spends a lot of time in class working through practice slowly and asking the class questions we can't answer because he doesn't teach. I only did well by going to others to get help and learning outside of class.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Sergey uses too much time asking questions and waiting for an answer that nobody knows because we havent been taught it yet. We got behind in class because of this so he skipped whole sections to make up for it. He does give extra credit for participation though.

Honestly, if you need to take calc 2 and you are not good at it, take this man. We had the highest test averages of all sections for the first 2 tests and a really good final average. Boring but good at his job.

Sergey is one of the nicest dudes you will ever meet. He is a respectful man and although he has a russian accent, its not very hard to understand! he gives extra points to your hw for participating in class and if you want to leave, just take your phone out and he will tell you go eat!! nice dude.

Highly ineffective. Asking questions that the class doesn't know takes up valuable time, spending 20 minutes on one problem that could have been solved in 5 is useless, and sending kids out of the classroom for personal pet peeves does not allow for effective classroom cooperation and meaningful learning. Get ready to skip class and read the book.

Not a terrible class, but the lectures are boring and slow. If you are good at math you will do fine in this class. It is a lot of studying outside of class. Basically no quizzes. the moon isn't real. Study hard and you can at least get a B.
ratingTags: TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Sergey gets way more heat than he deserves. The reality is he teaches a very tough class and does an alright job covering all of the material. Most of the bad reviews you see are people that aren't putting enough work into the class.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: The most respected math professor at Clemson. I loved his home videos at the beginning of the semester. If he asked me on a date I would say yes.
all im saying is that sergey is underrated. To be blunt, Sergey is Bae

Literally a meme of a professor, worst teacher that has ever existed. If you are amazing at math you may be able to bear it, but only because of the hilarious moments and ridiculous lectures that sergey gives. Be prepared to get kicked out of class for annoying him in the slightest. It's almost impossible to pay attention, use PAL leaders.

I took 10 minutes out of my exam study time to warn all of you beautiful people to PLEASE stay away from this teacher. The only good thing that had come out of his class is that he sometimes makes purposefully exploitable worksheets where it's possible to get (literally) 300 bonus points in order to boost his grade average. Do Not Take His Classes

Sergey is by far the worst teacher I've ever had. He has a thick accent which makes it hard to understand him and for him to understand the students. He asks students how to solve problems instead of teaching how to solve them. He writes a little bit of notes and then randomly stops and sits in his chair not teaching. AVOID HIM AT ALL COSTS.

I'm not even sure how Sergey has the qualification to teach at a high school much less a university. It takes forever to cover material because of his accent and he doesn't answers questions people have in class. Will skip material to stay on track with the course leaving you to teach yourself. WOULD NOT RECOMMEND.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: By having this professor, you will spend twice the amount of time covering material compared to MATH1060/1080 students from other classes. Avoid this professor at all costs, as it is his goal (and Clemson's) to waste as much of your time and money as possible.

He hardly speaks any English and his accent is so thick no one can understand him. He goes off on tangents in class and covers things unrelated to what is actually on the exams. If you took Calculus of One Variable in high school, you might be okay. If you didn't, prepare to struggle.

Sergey is truly a character. If you haven't taken calculus before, and this is assuming he's still teaching math 1060, be prepared to teach yourself all of the material. There is no way that he is qualified to teach 1060 and it is extremely difficult to understand him. You'll be lost most of the year so find someone else to teach you.

I took this class to satisfy an honors requirement and it ended up being way less work than the non-honors sections. We wrote two papers and had meetings with him to talk about revisions and then we resubmitted them for a grade. The discussions we had in class were really interesting and thought provoking. Take him for a fun class with minimal work

Austin is the best! His Honors section was awesome. Hilarious & super well-educated professor. Class discussions were always interesting. He wants all of his students to succeed. Gives excellent feedback. He's head of the Writing Center, so he's almost always available to help. He especially loves teaching Honors students. Take this class!!!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Hilarious

comment: Great professor!! Gives you the opportunity to revise papers and learn from mistakes to get a good grade. Class discussions make you think deeply. Take this class!!

Austin spent about 10-20 minutes of class taking attendance for a 30 person class just because he wants to ask how your life is, and he's really caring and funny. We didn't have as many papers as other classes. A couple small assignments and 2-3 big papers. He makes comments on rough drafts so you can make corrections. One of my favorites.

Austin is easily one of my favorite professors at clemson! Hes so much fun and hilarious. He tries to make everything relatable to his students, and genuinely wants to make sure his students are engaged. Would 100% take again!!!
Austin is the man. Easily one of the best English professors at Clemson. TAKE HIS CLASS!!!

He gives good feedback and will work with you if you make the effort. He's a funny guy, but he's not that great at teaching politics. He'd be the kind of person who it would be fun to discuss politics with outside of class. Goes off on tangents very easily.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--SO MANY PAPERS--Hilarious

comment: Great teacher! Understanding and helps whenever he can!

Took Austin for a class that, admittedly, is pretty pointless. It wasn't his fault, seeing as the class is being done away with by Clemson anyway.  He did a great job of trying to actually impart some wisdom upon us, and I always looked forward to his class. The man is absolutely hilarious and really gets to know his students.

One of the more difficult 1030 teachers, actually assigns papers, lots of homework, really friendly, tentative syllabus, willing to push due dates back, very funny, will sing to the class often, you can only miss 3 days of class

BEST PROFESSOR EVER!!!!!! take him!!!!! he is so smart and funny. He loves to have intellectual conversations with the class, but at the same time, he doesn't want anyone's grades to suffer if they don't quite understand. He is really easy, but his class is still really informative. TAKEEEEE HIIIIIMMMMMM

Prof Gorman is awesome & helpful. I hate english and honestly this is one of my favorite classes. We spend the class having casual discussions, you learn stuff without really realizing it, you'll actually get something from the course. Assignments are easy and he grades writing very fairly on improvement & effort, he understands its just a gened.

She offered tons of extra credit even though she was a hard grader. Last paper was heavily curved. Kind of strict about attendance and harped a lot on participation. Last project was definitely best part of the semester.
Ms. Powell was great and my favorite English professor! Super enjoyable discussions. Realistic expectations on projects. Would definitely recommend!

Dr. Smalls is a  good teacher. There is homework due every week and 6 quizzes over 13 chapters.  It is a common course class so the amount of homework and quizzes relative to other professors is relatively the same. Go to class if you want to pass ACCT 201 at Clemson. She can be a little fast but is an effective teacher. Taking again for 202.

Dr. Smalls isn't the best teacher, but by reading the book you can probably crack out an A. She reads directly off the power point, which is really wordy and difficult to take notes off of. There are "in class" assignments, but they can be completed outside of class. Go to SI if you're confused, but not the worst class ever.

Dr. Smalls offers extra credit, but Homework & quizzes are due every Sunday night, she reads from way too full powerpoints printed from Mcgraw-Hill, and goes really fast, she is not helpful at all, and she scheduled tests the day we returned from break and on Mondays. Not recommended at all.

Dr. Smalls has great knowledge of Accounting, however I do not like the way she tries to teach it.  She quickly moves through power points with a ton of information on each slide.  Homework and Quiz due every Sunday at 10PM.
Ms. McDonald is a good professor.  She grades papers quickly and fairly.  She is also willing to help you understand the material.

She posts her lecture guides online for you to print out and bring to class. If you can keep up and understand everything you will be fine. If you don't understand something you can ask her and she will try her best to help you.

Russell's Honors class is relatively difficult. I studied a ton for the tests and put a lot of effort in, so I got a pretty solid A. The tests are all short answer and you have to write a lot in a very short time. Other grades are all papers, both long and short. If you don't like to read/write, don't take this class. Otherwise, an A is feasible.

Her intro to sociology class may be easy but the sex and gender class that she offers should be avoided. The lectures are long and boring and she just likes to hear herself talk. Each time  students either answered a question or shared their thoughts, a sarcastic remark of some sort on her behalf was made. She makes this interesting topic painful.

Class can be boring but it is a really easy class. There are a lot of pop quizzes but they are easy if you did the assigned reading. The questions from the quizzes are used on the test and will save you. Easy tests. If you're looking for an easy A this is definitely the way to go.

I really enjoyed having Dr. Russell as my professor. As long as you keep up with the reading, an A in the class is easy to get. Lectures are a bit boring, but overall I would definitely recommend her if you want to take intro to Sociology.

The tests themselves aren't too difficult, but staying on top of the readings would be in your best interest, even if it is just a skim. Lectures can be boring, but she gives you the powerpoint and it is basically all the information you need.

Really couldn't stand this class. She is super sarcastic in a very rude way. Everything bothers her and she is such a slow grader. She takes off participation points if you miss class even though she says you have three "unexcused absences". Stupid group project and she grades it based off what she likes. The worst don't take her
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: Stephens is the worst, do NOT take her class. So much busy work and if you don't say all the things she wants then she docks your participation points. She has an awkward way of interacting with the class and always acts bothered by students. She should not be teaching this course. I would not suggest her especially if you're not an english major

This professor is disorganized. Discussion posts and group assignments were only given 2-5 days in advance. Had group projects with an online class that is very difficult because of conflicting schedules and not being able to physically meet with group. Final did not relate to material covered nor the same format as any other assignment.

Stephens is all about participation, as long as you speak once during class you will be fine. Tests are just papers/projects which she grades fairly easy. Weekly blog posts are for homework which are extremely easy. I would definitely recommend her. She lets you edit your papers to boost your grade at the end of the semester. NO FINAL!
Hard grading
Great and relatable professor. I never really liked English, but thanks to this professor, I found myself looking forward to the class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: This professor is amazing ! I had her for two English classes and she is very good at explaining things on point and goes out of her way to help you more understand anything you struggle with, if I had to take another English I would most definitely pick her.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Do not take Dr. Bock for MATH1040. He spends the whole class showing off his "intelligence" by doing problems that aren't applicable in any way to his students. He doesn't prepare his students for his exams and gives many pop quizzes in class on material he hasn't covered. Does have a large curve at the end though. If you have him, Lord have mercy!
Overall, awful teacher. He knows his stuff but can not teach material to save his life. Avoid unless you're just naturally good at calculous.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: He's actually not as bad as they say on here. He's just a kinda weird guy and it comes off as uncaring. He has a very dry sense of humor but really does know his calculus.  His quizes are hard but get rounded up like 2 letter grades at the end of the semester. Most people don't get his humor and decide to tune him out... this results in a bad grade

Just avoid him...  It's been 2 weeks and he hasn't taught anything. Quizzes are on things we haven't gone over yet. If you don't have a good background on the subject you are better off finding someone else. His teaching methods are questionable and his demeanor is unpleasant. AVOID.

This teacher was overall just awful. I had taken prevalence in high school and got a 96. I was more than prepared when it came to this class, but I was not able to handle it due to the material not being given out. We would do problems in class, then the quizzes would be completely different. Do NOT take this teacher!!

Will tell you everything that's going to be on his quizzes, and then proceeds to put none of those things on it. Terrible at explaining.  Before this class I had never made under an A in any math I've ever taken, but that changed very quickly.

In all fairness, Math 1080 is a very difficult class at Clemson and the tests are not written or graded by a single teacher. That said, Bock is a really bad teacher. You will not learn all the material you will need to pass the test by going to his lectures. His classes are disorganized and frustrating. Go to the academic success center to pass.

Terrible professor. Know to make inappropriate sexual comments. His office hours are mostly you asking questions while he is looking at imgur on his laptop. Avoid his class if you've never taken caculus before.

Bock is by far the worst professors Ive had. His office hours consists of snarrky comments on how you should already know the material ontop of him browsing imgur while you are attempting to yank any strand of information from. Is know to make very sexual refrences. Overall he is unprofessional and should be avoided like the plague.

I would avoid Bock at any opportunity. He is not a helpful teacher and wastes so much time. He has spent several class periods on 1 question, which he gets stuck on in the middle. Unless you can teach yourself you will have a difficult time in the class. He also does not explain things well.

She kept the course very interesting with interactive teaching methods like games and going up to the board. She also didn't mind slowing down and going into deeper explanation when students were confused on things.

Maria does a good job in preparing her students for the exams and quizzes. She has an accent which can be hard to understand at times, and she also speaks very fast which does not help. She uses many illustrations and videos which makes the material a lot easier to understand. Overall she is a great teacher that genuinely cares about her students.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: She's clear with what is expected for the tests and quizzes. Her lectures are often scattered and hard to follow, but you watch a lot of videos and she posts them online, which is a great way to study (it's how I passed the class). Would recommend her for ECON 211.

Involving the class in the lessons, having students write on the board, etc. was very helpful. Also, using videos and other elements besides just the powerpoint made the information more understandable and interesting. and she is hot!
if you put the work in that she requires, you can make an A in the class while learning a lot of material, too.

I would absolutely recommend this instructor to a friend. She's very thorough, she uses a variety of teaching methods, and she's very very kind and always willing to help. She is energetic and very attractive

Mrs. Droganova was very clear and organized.  Maria tried to make the class interactive and fun by playing games and videos. The option to be opted out of the final for those who had As at the end of the semester gave us the incentive to work hard in the class.
Great professor. Really enjoys the subject and takes her time to explain each topic in detail. Pay attention in class and you will do good.
Sometimes the material was hard. Go to her office hours and she will in depth go over whatever you are not understanding with different examples to make it relevant to you.

Professor Draganova is a great instructor. Maria works with all of the students to make sue we understand the concepts. Maria moves at a good pace and makes sure we all follow her. She is always available during and outside her office hours.
Maria is one of the best professors I have ever had. I want to major in Economics after taking her class. Expect to work hard though .

One of the best professors I have ever had. He made calculus easy for me and I have hated math my entire life. If you ever have questions he is there for you and will explain in very easy ways. Would take again in a second.

I loved Luke. Im not the best at math but he was a very clear teacher. He let me come to his office the days I missed class and went over the material with me. Its not his fault that the tests are hard its department wide. If you got to SI and talk to him you should pass. You have to work for it though. Take him, hes the best in the department.

Luke is a great calculus teacher especially if you already have knowledge of calculus from previous courses. He teaches it well and goes straight to the point. He also dismisses class early most days. Out of all the calculus teachers in the department I would definitely choose him.

One group project, two midterms, and a final. Seems like a great guy, knowledgable in macro. But you basically just learn from the book and his lectures just go over the reading to help us understand the harder topics, so you don't really need to show up. You can find the slides online, so his tests aren't extremely hard
Richard cares in a way not seen by many other professors. He is knowledgeable on a wide array of economics and could do great teaching any class, maybe even econometrics. Also, he's hot

Understands economics (obviously) but unfortunately not how to teach it - hands down the most confusing Econ lecture class I have ever attended.  Rude at times. Did not give partial credit for demonstrating understanding on tests; I got a 75 on a test I thought I'd gotten a 100 on due to one simple addition error in the beginning step of a problem.

Class was kind of boring but overall it was a good course. He explained exactly what was expected of you on tests. Reading the book is helpful but not necessary. If you are struggling he offers lots of office hours and really likes to help. I got an A with not much work besides studying the night before tests.

He's a really young instructor, but extremely intelligent. Economics is not easy for me, but he was always able to explain concepts in a way that would click. He is basically a mathematician and carries on at a quick clip, so reviewing algebra before this class will help!

Richard Sessa's teaching approach is to offer students a laboratory to consistently study and apply real world economic models. Richard consistently goes above and beyond for his students. However, in order to pass his class you must attend his lectures, complete the required readings and think outside the box.

Polymers was not the best class I've had, but it really wasn't as hard as people make it sound. To memorize the structures/reactions just practice writing them on a white board. He basically tells you what you need to know for each quiz and test, it's up to you whether you want to go through the old quizzes (go to his office for correct answers)
Really boring class that he curves at the end but you have to memorize all this useless information for his weekly difficult quizzes

He gives you questions from old quizzes and exams a week before the tests so you can study. If you want the answers, though, you need to try to get them from him ahead of time. He has way too many notes, most of which you don't need for the tests, but it's difficult to understand what you do need. He does curve at the end of the semester.

Professor Luzinov is an atrocious teacher. He is incredibly vague in his lectures, and his TAs are on a different page than he is when it comes to grading. There are quizzes every couple of weeks that are unreasonably hard, and then a midterm and final. He is beyond unhelpful when you go to his office hours. Better hope you can teach yourself.

Dr. Pinder is probably one of my top profs ever. She is hilarious, easy to talk to, and just constantly glows. I have yet to meet someone that doesn't love her. She wants to help students all you have to do is go up and talk to her. She laughs at anything so don't be afraid to crack a joke or bring up Coachella. I promise you she's very relatable.

Dr. Pindar is a terrific professor. She's easy to talk to and she really cares about her students. She's funny and she enjoys making the class laugh. In a small classroom setting, you have a chance to develop a real relationship with her and she will definitely be willing to help you later down the road.
I love this teacher!! She is so funny but she also knows how to teach. She is always available and will respond to your email very quickly. Take her, she is awesome!
LOVED HER! Take her if you can! She is very helpful and makes the material clear to students. Easy class because she's a great teacher!

She's so funny and makes every concept relateable to college students so you can understand it easier. Dr. Pindar genuinely cares about her students and she is super laid back. Always willing to help with whatever you need whether it's class related or not. The course is super easy, and she makes class enjoyable.

Do NOT procrastinate in this class! It is very self-paced, and everything is due at the end of the semester. Don't put it off, start it ASAP. I made that mistake and found myself scrambling to get everything done and turned in. If you procrastinate and you work better with strict due dates, don't take this class. She's an amazing professor though!

I took her class online and I'm really happy I did. As long as you do all that is asked of you it is pretty easy to get an A. Readings are interesting and I enjoyed being able to work at my own pace on assignments.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Caring

comment: I absolutely loved having her as my professor for my first English class. When doing research projects she didnt shy away from controversial topics, she let me write about a 60 year old sexist lingerie ad for our visual rhetorical analysis.

Dr. Aldebol-Hazle was a great professor to have freshman year! Very sweet and makes it easier to come to her 8am. She does give a fair amount of homework, however isn't hard, just time consuming. Overall a great professor and a sweet lady!

Kristen was an exceptional professor. She cared for each of her students and strived to make the classroom a fun and high-energy environment. The lessons were focused and engaging. It is an easy class to pass and the material is interesting to learn. There a quite a few papers but no more than what is expected in a literature class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: She is such an enthusiastic teacher, and truly made lectures interesting! If you do the work, it is almost impossible to make any lower than a B.

She is a great teacher! The only thing that is frustrating about her is she does not return your assignments to you for at least a month. She will give you feedback on your first paper and ways to improve your paper on the day your second paper is sue, which is not helpful. Other than that she is a great teacher and really cares for her students!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: Kristen is an amazing professor and really cares for her students and always willing to help.  However, she does assign a ton of assignments that can really pile up.  She also is a very slow grader, which isn't helpful if you are hoping to except the final and still don't know your grade in the class until the day before the actual final.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: Wonderful teacher, always willing to talk about what is going on in the reading and in class. Very bubbly personality that wakes you up at 8AM! Turned my literature credit into my favorite class of the semester, I would highly recommend if you don't mind writing and discussion.

I took Kristen's class online over the summer. She provides good feedback on assignments but has absolutely way too many and likes to micro-manage. I personally don't like her kind of teaching and the amount of assignments was ridiculous, especially if you are taking more than one class. Assignments are easy, just feels like a waste of time.

Kristen was cool. I had her at 8 AM, so her strict grading policy was a real pain. BUT, she teaches the material well and most people (the ones that participated and showed up to class) got an A. If you're super anal about getting grades back though, would not recommend. Didn't know I was exempting until the night before my final.

She was amazing at first. Then, she started changing due dates, changing requirements, and not really helping too much. She assigned way to much to work, that she then didn't grade in a timely manner. I was getting feedback for the first of three assignments as the third was due already. I would not recommend her.

Best professor I've ever had. I would consider a friend as well as a professor. She made me care about material that I otherwise would not have. This was a gen ed requirement for me, but it ended up being my favorite class.

Kristen is the best English teacher/professor I've had in my whole life. This class was actually interesting and I'm a science major. She always is looking for ways to connect with her students and she is a truly awesome person.
Nice person. Easy engineering class so not much work but could teach a little better and make sure students grasp material. Assigns group projects but that's from the department.
Very nice and genuine. He went over study guides before each test.
He brought us all pizza one Friday because someone said Fridays were boring. Cool dude.
This guy rocks. I promise you won't regret taking him. He's young, funny, really helpful and the class isn't tough at all. He actually makes computers fun. Best teacher for this subject by far.

Uses a lot of slides and expects you to print them. very disorganized with the lectures. Doesn't care if students are learning. hard to understand his accent. worst professor ever, he should be forced to retire. he is only teaching because it is a requirement for him. it is a shame Clemson has this type of professors
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--So many papers

comment: He does give a lot of homework, but he is very excessible outside of class for help and is very lenient about how he grades the homework. He makes his lectures interesting and not boring. After hearing about some of my other friends precalc professors, I would definitely recommend Andy. He's very organized and knows what he's talking about!
ratingTags: LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Amazing lectures

comment: Really cool guy, always willing to help.  Very good about grading and timelines, very reasonable and cooperative about giving points back.  He's a great guy if you give him a chance.

THIS GUY IS AWFUL. He is by far the worst teacher I have ever taken and will ever take. He does not know how to explain it and during our review for the final there were 4 things he said he did not know how to do, soI left. The coordinator came to class and corrected him 3 times and he is still here. HE IS AWFUL. SHOULD NOT BE TEACHING. DROP NOW.

I am telling you if you love life and you love your GPA do NOT take this man class. He is the absolute worst teacher on campus. We counted one lecture and the man said "um" 170 times. Save yourself the time and frustration. BEWARE!!!!!!! He will legit explain an entire confusing math thesis and at the end tell you that you don't need to know it.

I LOVE Dr. Pangborn (now married). She is the most caring and empathetic professor I've ever had. She took an entire class period and demonstrated how to run a focus group by having a focus group with the class on how our semester was going. She taught me so much about qualitative research and if you can take her class you should!
She is honestly amazing, inspirational, and truly cares about her students, which can be hard to find. I would take her for any class available.

Dr. Pangborn is PHENOMENAL! She loves her class material and students. This class isn't necessarily as hard as other COMM classes, but it is really interesting. It changes how you think about health and illness (She got married and is now Dr. Pangborn). Definitely loves participation and teaches somewhat socratically

Very passionate and caring lecturer, gave the most detailed and helpful feedback for papers. Though not accessible outside class and rarely replied emails. Expectations for assignments are unclear and course is not so structured.

I love Dr. Pangborn!! She really cares about her students and is willing to help you succeed! Her tests are pretty hard, and are free response so detail really matters. If you do the class readings and participate in discussions you will be fine. 10/10 would recommend!

I loved Faiza! She is funny and tries to make the class more personal and relatable. She really knows what she's talking about and it's obvious that she cares about the subject as well as your well being in the class. If she notices that people aren't following, she'll go back and elaborate. Tests aren't too hard and she's always available for help

Mrs. Shoji is an awesome teacher!  She's kind, fun, and easily laughs and clearly has fun teaching.  Lectures are very helpful and grammar is built around vocabulary.  The lecture format makes things very helpful, and she makes us perform various, and sometimes humorous, actions for the rest of the class to describe in Japanese.  Take her class!

Mrs. Shoji is an incredible teacher.  At first, she gave me a strict Japanese teacher vibe, which got to my head and I slumped in the class.  However, one day she brought it up with me, and that showed me how nice a person she is.  Academically, her lectures are great.  They focus on vocabulary and grammar.   Looking forward to next semester!

Terrible teacher... just reads slides (roughly 150 slides per chapter or more) and tests you on random parts of the slides. Random assignments that count for participation and grades very strict on packaging line project.

Very boring. Simply reads an abundance of Powerpoint slides for the entire class. Does not give you much help in actually understanding the information. Attendance is not mandatory, but there are in class "activities" that he will "surprise" the class with (usually on Fridays) to take attendance. Should be an online, self-taught class.

Makes slides straight from textbook. EXTREMELY boring. Study key points and machine pictures. Doesn't take attendance but gives out random worksheets that he counts as attendance (this will shift grade up or down letter grade at the end of the year-he gives them almost every Friday). Not a great teacher but cracks himself up and has an absurd laugh

Very boring class, you'll lose focus too easy. He reads straight off the slides so it's not worth going to class, but he gives 5 surprise in-class worksheets so if you don't go then you'll get a 0 for participation which will hurt your class. Tests aren't hard, but they're very intuitive so you have to know your material.

Every single lecture slide had errors (which you can't get powerpoint format because he doesn't want his work "copyrighted")- every single test had a different format - new format for test were not given until 1-2days before test MAX - no questions during exams "because he has two versions" - openly talks down about nutrition majors (1/2 the class)

Unless you enjoy memorizing numerous tables and being confused on what the test is on, DO NOT TAKE. One of the least helpful professors I've ever had. He does not teach you to understand the material, only to memorize it. Outlines and powerpoints are unorganized and difficult to understand. This class required more stress than it should have.

He is genuinely a nice guy. The class is difficult, and he's not the greatest at lecturing. However, if you ask questions and engage he is more than willing to help and explain. He appreciates feedback from the class and wants students to do well on the exam.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: This class is extraordinarily difficult, which most people know going into it. Michael genuinely want you to succeed and he's a nice person. He is not the best lecturer, but it's a hard class to make super interesting. If you ask for help he will do a great job guiding you and making a plan. Just communicate on what you need and he will adjust!!
He is the nicest, most helpful teacher I have ever had and cares so much about the success of his students!

This class was ridiculous for a college course. When going into this, I thought it would be a lot better since i had already taken calculus. Even knowing about calculus did not prepare me for the difficulty of the course. He did not prepare us for the tests and did not have structured notes. When you asked him a question he did not know the answers

I did fine in calculus in high school, passed the AP exam, and yet this class was awful. He is so confusing and wastes time on information irrelevant to what is covered on exams. The WebAssign homework is way easier and different than what is on exams for whatever reason. He gets in class problems wrong and flies through the info actually needed.

He teaches with proofs and makes the class ten times harder than it has to be. Also, he has a stuttering problem where he literally sensors his own sentences and you have to guess what he said. It makes it really hard to learn calculus.

I have never met anyone that has made me feel so dumb in my life. He will continually go over material that is not on the test, then go over everything on the test within the last 2 days before the exam. He has a hard time communicating material to his students. He gives no additional practice work other than the mandatory web assign. SLOW GRADER.

Awful professor. Does not come to class prepared in anyway. Most of the time what ever he writes down or works out is wrong. He makes random things up when he teaches or "off the top of his head" Works out every problem without explaining a single step even if you just learned it. You better have taken calc before or plan to teach yourselfb!

He does not know how to teach calculus. If you haven't ever taken calculus in high school before, you will not pass. He skips steps and if you ask questions he is mean and does not explain the answers at all. Wasn't prepared for the tests at all.

I highly recommend this professor for many reasons.  Not only is he still a law enforcement officer, which helps him relate to the course material, but he also has a great connection with students.  He does not give too much work, just enough to keep you on track.  If he were to teach another course, I would definitely choose him as my professor.
Her accent is so heavy, I spent more time trying to figure out what she was actually saying instead of learning the actual material.
Her accent is so heavy, I spent half the time trying to figure out what she is actually saying instead of learning the material.

Math 1080 is very hard, but this professor does not help at all. Her strong accent made it difficult to understand sometimes. However, her teaching abilities were not strong. She is a graduate student with little background in teaching. Shes as sweet as can be, and always willing to help, but her teaching needs some work. Try to skip if you can!

He is a great professor and allows you to have a lot of freedom, which I appreciated. He gives you the materials you need to succeed, and he allows you to take your tests at home. I am someone who does not usually like taking tests, but having the stress-free environment was a weight lifted off my shoulders. His lectures are helpful and interesting

Professor Kohlmeyer is really good. I took his Managerial Accounting class. Attendance it not required. The HW is not difficult and the tests are also un-proctored online take-home tests. He always does at east half of our HW in class and the lectures are always fascinating.

One of the worst teachers I have ever had. I busted my butt watching the videos and taking tons of notes and I never passed a test. Luckily, there are a few cases and a lot of homework to pad your grade so I will still pass, but dang. Tests are SUPER tricky and nothing like the homework. This class was HELL!
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--Tests are tough

comment: Would recommend.  Tests are challenging, however lower test grades are balanced out by the homework, group projects, and connect videos.  I received a C on the first test (hardest) but still managed to get an A overall.  Lectures can be a little dry, but Dr. Kohlmeyer clearly knows this topic.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Be prepared to spend extensive time on reading and homework.  Tests are nothing like the practice quizzes or homework, or even the sample exams provided.  He does realize tests are difficult, and provides opportunities such as homework and case studies to bring up your average.

Took her twice, just a fantastic choice if you're looking for a supportive environment to learn Spanish. She goes out of her way to help you with pronunciation and vocabulary, and she even explains the difficult grammar concepts in English. She assigned two fairly easy projects, and her exams are more than fair. I'll definitely take her again.
Nice prof and relatively easy grader. Get ready to work for your grade tho and participate in class. You learn a lot of material but it becomes a nuisance as course progresses
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: seriously one of the nicest teachers here!!! i've learned more in one semester with her than I have in my other 5 years of being in Spanish classes. the quizzes and tests are easy if you study and keep up with the lessons, and the in-class activities she does help A LOT with learning the material making it even easier!

Y'all. Fama is my girl. I highly recommend her, especially if you struggle with Spanish, but even if you don't. She teaches in a way that drills it into your head, and if you just listen and participate in class it'll be an easy A. Not because it's easy, but because she teaches the material well. Seriously participate though. Volunteer answers.

Professora Fama is a great choice for Spanish 2020! She provides a lot of in-class activities, and she allows you to work in groups at all times (other than exams/quizzes). Her quizzes are pretty easy, and she clearly states what you need to know before exams and prepares you for them accordingly. Do NOT speak in English at all during class!

TAKE HER!!!! My favorite Spanish professor after taking 4 semesters at Clemson. Fama is super helpful, typically very lenient when it comes to using English in the classroom. Very reasonable amount of work. Offers many opportunities for extra credit- take advantage of all of these. It will seriously boost your grade. Allowed 2 unexcused absences.
Highly recommended. She made 2020 easier than the others.

Professor Fama is extremely helpful and an all around great teacher!  She makes learning Spanish fun with games and activities!  She is always organized and prepared for class.  I highly recommend her and would definitely take her again!

Profesor Fama is the best Spanish teacher i've had so far. She's so nice and patient and she is more than willing to help you with anything. She does talk in all Spanish, but she talks slow enough and annunciates to where you can understand. I learned so much in her class. She's the best!
Jamie is amazing! She is super sweet and isn't a tough grader. I would definitely recommend her for this class!

Jamie is great and really cares about helping you progress in psychology. Class would only meet once a week more often than not because we would cover all the material in a single class. No tests or quizzes, just an easy assignment every week and a small reflection for the midterm and final.

Super nice and easy to talk to if you have any problems/concerns she is totally approachable.  No tests or final, just papers and weekly assignments.  Highly recommend.  She often will cancel class on Fridays if we get through the material in the beginning of the week.  Attendance is taken for participation grade.

I enjoyed taking PSYC 2020 with Ms. Fynes. There are weekly assignments (short and straightforward - an easy 10/10 points), a Midterm Reflection, and a Final Reflection. There were no quizzes or tests. Ms. Fynes does a nice job keeping the class engaged and she is extremely nice! She also responds quickly to e-mails. An A is definitely attainable.
An excellent teacher. Very understanding. Assignments are easy to complete, and she gives time in class to get them done. Super sweet and willing to help with anything you need.

I liked him at the beginning of the semester, but then I realized he will choose favorites and only helps them out. He assigns so many stupid projects and they were so time consuming and would make them due the next class day.  These projects also had nothing to do with english.  Overall, do not take him!!! He is the definition of extra.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: I loved Professor Quigley, and he made me love English for the first time.  His assignments were all really cool- used adobe stuff- only a few papers.  He was super creative and supportive of making mistakes and learning how to fix them.  He is definitely one of the best English teachers I've ever had.  If you have to take Engl 1030- TAKE HIM!!
Great guy. Means well for the students, everything done has a purpose. Very supportive.

Like the prior poster mentioned, Mine is arrogant and does not offer help or clarification. She insinuates that students are unintelligent if they do not immediately grasp course material. We do not all have degrees in geophysics. If you do not agree with her views on issues, she will bend grading criteria to "punish" you.

Dogan has a degree in geophysics, she's extremely intelligent and knows her stuff, but with all that intelligence comes high arrogance. She does not help easy and will sometimes laugh at questions you ask. Not to mention she's from Russia and is really hard to understand. Good part about her class is she teaches right from the book. SO READ ALOT.

My favorite professor at Clemson. He also co-taught PRTM 822 (Strategic Planning). His extremely detailed instructions make it easy to know exactly what is expected, which is a lot. He is a tough but fair grader, meaning that you actually learn instead of just getting your ego stroked. Always available for advice. I highly recommend him!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Clear grading criteria

comment: Provides very clear instructions for what is expected on projects.  Be very thorough and use high attention to detail and you should do well.  He does expect high quality writing, so if you have poor writing/communication skills, you may have a hard time with projects.  An excellent professor overall.
Tuff class to sit through but an easy A. Very confusing on what needs to be done for papers and projects.

Dr. Briley is very knowledgeable about her subject material and enjoys talking about it. Very soft-spoken and lectures tend to be boring. Gives very clear grading criteria and basically tells you exam questions for studying. Fairly easy grader. Just do the work and you will be fine.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: I LOVED Dr. Briley! She is super sweet and you just know she cares about her students and is very knowledgable in special education. There is a semester long project but it is spaced out so you'll have TONS of time to get it done w/ feedback. She loves to help and answer questions, and tests are very very easy!

Dr. Ingram-Smith is awesome, really does teach the material very well and genuinely cares about her students' success. Always go over your exams with her, she'll almost always give you points back. Only complaint is that she tends to downplay her very difficult exams. Exams are tough, but you'll actually learn the material. Best option for 3010.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Graded by few things--Caring

comment: DO NOT LISTEN TO THE BAD REVIEWS! Dr.I-S is amazing. She explains biochem in an understandable way; if you don't get it, she is always available for office hours! She is really understanding so if you need help or if she messed up grading, she'll usually be extremely generous to help you out! One of the best in the department.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Although she has no office hours, Dr. I-S assured us she would be able to meet outside of class if we needed it. This was not the case as she was too busy. She tried to be helpful by telling us how to study for her exams, but she often downplayed the difficulty of them. She really is a very nice woman, but that doesn't mean she's a good professor.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Dr. Ingram-Smith is a very nice person and is super approachable. She has student run review sessions before her exams which are super helpful. Her exams are really difficult and long and require you to apply what you learn in lecture (all questions are short answer). Memorization will not work and the textbook doesn't help much.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Dr. I-S is an absolutely amazing woman. She is definitely willing to help, sit with you, and talk about your grade on an exam (sometimes she give back points when you're in the right). Her lectures are pretty decent, just make sure to pay attention. Her exams are tough, and if given the chance, study off of previous exams. Gives good study guides

Jonathan is literally the best professor I've ever had in my entire life. I would 10000000000% times recommend him to anyone needing to take Econ 2110. He simplifies things and makes the material much easier to understand. He has a very dry sense of humor and it's the BEST!!!!! he posts lectures online but deletes parts so make sure to be in class.

I loved this class. Was not too difficult if you study. Gives a lot of quizzes and homework assignments that boost your grade. Quizzes were a lot harder than the tests. Uses great examples and overall made class pretty interesting. He lets you drop the final at the end if you have an A in the class.

He does a good job of making boring lectures interesting. The class is not mandatory, but if you show up and at least just listen then you will pass. Just try a little and you will make an A. Do well on the quizzes and homework

Need to take ECON211? I strongly recommend taking it with this prof. The course covers a lot and you must be able to conceptualize, but he provides necessary resources to help you succeed. Welcomes questions and seems to actually enjoy the subject. Engages the class with a sarcastic sense of humor and many relative examples (+ pictures of his dog!)

Favorite professor that I've had so far. Really funny guy that makes himself seem awkward on purpose and its hilarious. Makes lectures easy to follow, time goes by fast, and he makes the information actually seem interesting by using a bunch of good examples. Going to class definitely helps, but he posts the lecture slides online. Easy to get an A.
It was really great class I've ever seen. If there is anyone who is going to take the Principle of Microeconomic class, I will definitely recommend the professor.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Lots of homework--Amazing lectures

comment: Professor Ernest is probably the best teacher I've had at Clemson. The class is not hard and he does not make attendance mandatory. If you get the chance, TAKE HIM!

Ernest is definitely a character and he is engaging in class and attendance isn't necessary. The book was not needed. He posts all the lectures online and goes over them in class and he's always upfront about tests and quizzes and what's expected on them. Not a lot of homework besides studying. BEST econ professor at Clemson!
What a gem... Ernest made this subject as interesting as possible. The quizzes and test were for the most part very straight forward. Attendance is not mandatory. Funny guy.

Overall, he was a good teacher. He does not take attendance. As long as you read over the textbook before quizzes and exams you will be fine. He is very laid back and makes lectures enjoyable. He posts the lectures online but not fully complete. I would take him again if I could.

Ernest was my favorite professor this semester! His humor made class entertaining, and he was able to make econ not so boring. You can also exempt the final exam with a high A. Definitely take him if you can!!

Ernest is a great professor. Definitely tries his best to be funny and engaging with his course material. Definitely knows his stuff. Homework is very easy and does not take much time, but helps to understand course material. The expectations for quizzes and exams are very well laid out and easy to prepare for.

Really gave great examples for the class that made the content exponentially more understandable. He also allows exemptions for those with A's or high A's in his class (so, nice motivation to do well).

Professor Ernest was a great teacher. He explains everyone very well and is always willing to answer questions. You have to be willing to put in some work but his lecture slides are very detailed and help a lot.
He was a really nice guy who really cares about his students. He is in a good mood all the time, funny guy. Lectures get long at points, but he is good at the lectures, good examples.

Professor Ernest is a great instructor! He knows how to teach the information in a clear, but concise manner. He relates the topics to real life scenarios quite often which really helped me understand micro a whole lot better. 10/10 would def recommend and would honestly retake his class!

This man is the best ever!!! He is SOO good at explaining concepts. His tests, for the most part, are straight up and not very tricky. He is hilarious and he is probably the best professor at Clemson. Might possibly change my major to Econ bc of him. 1000000/10 would recommend

Jonathan was an AMAZING econ professor. His classes were entertaining, especially for a traditionally dry topic. You definitely have to study for the quizzes and tests, but his powerpoints are extremely helpful and easy to understand. I would 100 percent take his class!!

Mr. Ernest was great. Good humor during lectures which were very straight forward. Hes also easy going while remaking very professional. He wont do your work for you. However if you put in the effort youll have no problem getting an A.
Professor Ernest was great! The class is straight forward. If you study the worksheets you will do well on tests and quizzes. I would definitely take this professor again.

hes an awesome professor! it was definitely my favorite class of the semester. i definitely took advantage of the fact that attendance isn't mandatory but i wish i hadn't. i still did well in the class but his lectures were really interesting and he makes it fun and easy to understand. hes also really funny and is very approachable if you need help
He is always open to answering questions and really wants to help you understand the material. He shows pictures of his dog, too. Overall an awesome professor.

He is super nice and I love him. He always includes random pictures of his dog in the powerpoints, and I went to his office hours for extra help one day, and there was a kitten in there. I had never taken an econ class before this, and he made the lecture material really easy to understand. I would highly recommend taking this class.

Mr. Ernest is very organized and overall a great professor. His powerpoints are very helpful & contain all of the information that are on the exams/quizzes. Although attendance isn't mandatory, I found it beneficial to listen to him explain the material.

Rightly rated teacher so far. He is able to make death by powerpoint work somehow, even having to be an early morning class. His notes are dense, so it's not just random information that will not be on a quiz/test. What you are tested on, he has given to you in class. Personality wise, he's got a dry humor. I found that pleasing. Take econ with him

I took this class because my major (Pre-Pharmacy) required it. I wasn't expecting much out of it but Professor Ernest made the class one of my favorites. While attendance is not mandatory, if you show up and pay attention you WILL get an A in the class and be able to exempt the final. The only hw outside of class is online and due on Sundays.

Mr. Ernest is a fantastic teacher. Cares about his students and really wants them to succeed. You have to try in this class but he makes it very possible to get an A, just do all the work. Only about 1 hr of homework a week due Sunday nights online. Tells a lot of jokes to keep things exciting and gives really good examples for harder concepts.

He really cares about his students and their success in his class. Flexible and welcoming office hours. His lectures go with his PowerPoint Slides and helps students to gain a better understanding through examples.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Tests? Not many

comment: Really great teacher! Go to lectures and just red over the chapters and you'll get good grades on the test! Plus you can exempt the final if you have a high A

Professor Ernest is great to take an economics class with. Easy powerpoint notes that he also posts on online.  Exempt from the final if you have an A . Funny guy, tries to make class as interesting as possible

Great guy.  Tries to make the material more interesting by using funny examples and lots of pictures.  He makes lots of dad jokes and they are pretty great tbh.  If you come to class and pay attention you will get a good grade no problem. Homework is only about an hour a week (maybe a little more) and all exams are multiple choice.

I'm a science major and took this class to fill a gen ed but it ended up being one of my more entertaining classes. His humor and tangents make the material a little more bearable even in a class as boring as Econ. He allowed students with A's to exempt the final, so just study hard for tests and do the homework and you'll be good.

Jonathan Ernest was the highlight of my semester. Sure it was an 8 am econ class, but his corny dad jokes, random pictures on slides, and photos of his dog that he included as incentives to answer correctly made my semester. He offered extra credit, offered an exemption on the final if you made an A, and helped me out at the end. 10/10 recommend.

Great teacher. Always has some perspective that is fresh and knowledgeable. Took 4 classes with him and it was a ridiculous pleasure. Projects and tests are easy. Some reading but most of it isn't really needed and is interesting. Great guy. Lectures can be boring sometimes but it's a good time to do other work.

He is a knowledgeable and friendly professor but tends to have slow lectures that drag on. Attendance is not mandatory however he does give a good amount of pop quizzes. There is a major group project towards the end of the semester in this class and it is the only time I ever used the text book.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Dr. Johnson is probably the nicest professor at Clemson. He is very smart and really cares about his students. His lectures can be boring and he can drone on but he is a great guy! I have had him for ENR 1010, 1020, 4500, & 4290. You have to try very hard to get less than an A or B in his classes and if you do you're not putting in any effort.
He is a very knowledgeable teacher and has many years of experience, but he tends to drone on. He truly cares about his students and their success.

easily the most condescending teacher I've ever had. Just make sure you write down his exact opinion when you take notes because his is the only one that matters. It's easy enough to pass but answer test questions with his opinions or he'll mark them wrong even if you can defend your stance

Terrible teacher. So rude to students who needed help with the material. For an entry level course, this was harder then chemistry. His opinion was what mattered on the paper, even though he told us we could write from either stand point.

Enjoyed the class and learned a lot. Munson says interesting things but is pretty boring. He just talks. Assigned readings every day of class with quizzes. Quizzes are three questions and you grade them yourself. Towards the end of the semester I didnt even read, just wrote in my own answers. One paper, 6 pages long, not too bad, 2 exams and final
The best math professor at Clemson!!!

One of the best professors I've had to date. Highly recommend for a daunting subject like Diff Equ. Attendance is not mandatory but the lectures are extremely valuable and there are in-class learning activities nearly every day which are easy 100s so go to class. Do the homework, suggested practice problems, and write study guides if you want an A.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: This was probably the best instructor I've had in my college career (so far). He is available quite often, answers your questions well and makes sure you're prepared for exams. We had "learning activities" every day in class, but you work with a partner and it is almost a guaranteed 100. Show up, listen, ask questions. This guy was great.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Caring

comment: Sean is an awesome teacher especially for Diff Eq. He set the class up in a way that provoked actual learning. Everyday there are partner activities that will ensure you are keeping up with the material as you go along. The notes he gives are pretty good. He doesn't make things complicated. Tip: be really good with derivative and integral basics.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Clear grading criteria

comment: Sean took time to explain topics to make sure everyone had a strong foundation. Every week, there was a quiz and homework out of the book was due (sometimes a lot). We had 2 tests and a final and on each test, there were 11 questions but he graded out of 10. He had test review days. 5% of the final grade is coming to class. Overall a good teacher!

Doesn't understand that her students are not English majors. Has ridiculous amounts of homework per week. Spent more time doing work for her than for my engineering classes. Essays are difficult, because she has this weird model that she uses and way of interpreting text that doesn't make much sense.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: She may seem intimidating at first but she is very willing to help you succeed. The way she structures her papers are difficult to grasp but once you get the hang of it you will be fine. I started with an F and finished the class with an A. Always participate and talk in class.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria

comment: She will scare you at the beginning  (1/2 my class dropped). There is weekly homework responses that are completion grades (she doesn't tell u til last week of class). The 2 essays were fairly short but different than your typically essay. She wants to see effort- if you participate in class and visit her office, you will do fine in the course.

She's a great teacher and person. There is a lot of homework and reading but you can do it. There was only 2 essays in my class and they are short. Its tough getting use to her style of writing but she prepares you well. She changes the theme of the class every semester but the books my semester were every interesting and I really liked them.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Participation matters

comment: The only chance to get a good grade is finish the assignment under the model given by herself which is terrible for a business class. If you miss a portion of the requirement, you will lose all the credits. She is more willing to give you a bad credit than telling you how to make the work better.

I loved Professor Wiley! She's very opinionated and she loves to push her agenda, but I really enjoyed getting to know her as a person. As long as you talk in class, she'll really like you and you will consequently do just fine on the papers. I had no problem getting an A in the class. Don't let the other reviews scare you--I'd take her again.

Forgot about a test but gave us a pop quiz on a book we didn't read instead. Expects students to read her mind about when things are due. She is very steadfast in her ways, even when she is totally and completely incorrect. There is no way to prepare because she doesn't stick to the syllabus. Avoid her class at all costs.
Prof Wiley, terrible teacher who is difficult to communicate with due to her being rude and judgmental. avoid at all costs

He cares about his students and his performance. He tries to not make the lectures awfully boring and he is able to relate to the students, which is key in being a good professor. The class is pretty easy and April is very nice.
She does not have the typical english class that just has you write papers and read books. We, instead, analyzed different things buy creating videos through PremierePro.

comment: Dr. Gale is really knowledgeable and you can tell she loves what she does. If you love English and American history, this is the class for you. comment: Amazing Professor, really strives to get to know all her students. There is a lot of reading but it is a American Literature class. comment: DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS UNLESS YOU WANT TO DROWN IN WORK. She assigns essays for homework. Quizzes are 5 questions for an entire 300 page book. comment: She's a nice person but gives insane amounts of homework for a class that's supposed to be low stress. She also gives 6 question quizzes on readings of 30 pages. I don't recommend this class unless you have a lot of free time to spend doing homework or get a different teacher if possible.

comment: I absolutely LOVED Dr. Gale... she was the first professor at Clemson I really clicked with. She expects you to participate, but class is always a great conversation. comment: Dr. Gale was a great professor. She really cares about her students and wants them to succeed. comment: Prof. Gale is good at teaching and really loves what she does, but she's not really outstanding. If I found out I was in one of her classes, my biggest reaction would be a sense of comfort that at least one of my professors was competent.

comment: He was awful. His final exam made no sense & covered cumulative topics which he never discussed would be on the exam. Do not take his class.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Professor Barrett takes his time and will not move on to a new subject unless everyone understands what he has gone over. comment: Kraemer is a solid choice. Not fantastic, not awful. The class is very group-project intensive. It becomes a lot easier if you pick a good group. She has quizes every class,so you have to go

You will have quizzes every day. A few will be dropped at the end of the semester, but you need to show up and take the quizzes to pass. First half is based on software lifecycle and is straightforward, then you get hit by the RESOLVE verification language truck so you need to set up a good grade before the second half. Very thoughtful professor.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Is she a good person? Yes. Is she a good professor? That's debatable. Attendance was basically mandatory because we had a quiz almost every class. ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: Dr. Kraemer is terrible. She is about as good at answering questions as a politician. I wouldn't bother taking her class if it's not required. She puts no emphasis on any of the material on the test, is incredibly boring, and rambles. She assumes you have previous computer science experience, and is incredibly difficult to follow for a beginner.

Although her lectures are hard to sit through she a good teacher. The lecture notes are important and include examples that show up on tests. She gives quizzes (some announced, some pop)  but they are not difficult. Her tests are so easy and just like the practice ones given. She does also curve test scores more so than other professors.
Dr. Pani is very caring and always available to answer to our questions.
Worst professor ever. They expect students to memorize 200+ slides, absolute worst professor there is.

comment: Dr. Pani isn't the most interesting lecturer, but the material is interesting. She gives announced quizzes and one or two pop quizzes. Her exams are super easy. comment: Dr. Pani is a very nice professor. Very nice lecture notes and clear examples helped me a lot.

Multiple choice comprises a large portion of the tests, and the questions are poorly written, often requiring some obscure knowledge of the subject matter. I don't recommend her.
Very accessible, wants everyone to pass. Tests are very straightforward.
Hard to understand, couldnt care less about students, definitely would not recommend this professor.

comment: She may be a little hard to understand at times, but she is the best option for MSE 2010 at Clemson. She is super nice and her tests are very straightforward and not super specific or in-depth. Just go to class, turn in her classworks (which she gives you the answers to) and study the practice tests she gives you and you'll do fine.

Professor Pani is very quiet. Her lesson plans usually seem very jumbled. The homework is usually easy, but inconsistent. She frequently contradicts herself and spends extra time on the simplest material and leaves the most difficult for you to find out on your own. Slides she gives you don't always match her lecture slides.

I had him as a TA for my bio lab last semester and he was very good. He spoke extremely fast, which was hard to keep up with most times. However, he got us started and finished with every lab very quickly. Overall a good TA and tries to make the lab as easy for you as he can.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: I really do not recommend taking this professor if at all possible. By far the very worst professor I've had during my time in Clemson. comment: Schwall is a bro. He is real relaxed and his class is really easy. He makes it really clear what you need to know, I got a 98 or above on all his tests.

comment: Plis is an alright choice. The only problem I have with him is the fact that he wants extremely specific things in his projects yet is very vague when he explains the instructions. comment: I enjoyed this class and Plis's lecture style. Criteria was clear and fair. The lab on the other hand is what killed me. It is timed and you must finish within the lab time. Do not skip class. He uses Reef for pop quizzes and you can only see the questions if you are in class, so go. His instructions are vague, so the class was kind of difficult for me. Read the PPTs (quizzes). Class was more difficult than it needed to be. He also lied to me saying the final wasn't similar to the 2 midterms but they're identical.

How to pass: Show up to class and listen. The lectures are so well organized, and honestly quite entertaining that you will never need to study if you go. (He posts all the slides online too) However, there are in class "pop-quizzes" every day on Reef: you've been warned. Would take again, wasn't too difficult but the homework is time consuming.

comment: Kevin really isn't really that bad. He had to work with Murali with 2150 so he really had no choice but to follow what he said. He did the best he could to make the class bearable. He was always willing to help with the projects and easily accessible through email. Totally recommend
